Fix CVE-2025-69223: Decompression bomb (zip bomb) vulnerability

This patch adds protection against decompression bombs by limiting the
maximum decompressed output size to 32MiB per decompress call. This prevents
an attacker from sending a small compressed payload that expands to exhaust
server memory.

Origin: upstream, https://github.com/aio-libs/aiohttp/commit/2b920c39002cee0ec5b402581779bbaaf7c9138a
Author: Sam Bull <git@sambull.org>

