Backport of upstream commit 1ac92dae2f30f311cfda08e7a431e76b9cb41a28
("Payload close on disconnect", PR #12831; 3.14 backport: a762eda5).

Fixes CVE-2026-54280: Response.write_eof() did not close the Payload body
when the underlying write() raised (e.g. client disconnect mid-write or
task cancellation). The payload's close() was therefore skipped, leaking
file descriptors / other resources held by the payload. Wrapping the
write call in try/finally guarantees close() runs on every code path.

Adapted to aiohttp 3.12.14: the runtime hunk applies verbatim. The test
hunk imports asyncio, Payload, and AbstractStreamWriter (none were
imported in 3.12.14's test module), and uses the locally-imported
Response symbol instead of web.Response (matches 3.12.14 import style).
The CHANGES/12831.bugfix.rst changelog file from the upstream commit is
intentionally omitted.

Origin: upstream, https://github.com/aio-libs/aiohttp/commit/1ac92dae2f30f311cfda08e7a431e76b9cb41a28
Bug: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-54280

